                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I, like most other enchanters, was extremely disappointed with the stealth removal of charm from the majority of GoD zones.
<br />
I'm working under the assumption that it was a "quick fix" because in its current state charm was overpowered with these mobs and there will be a proper fix in the near future.  (maybe I'm dreaming here?)
<br />

<br />
I'll agree that that having 1000+ dps pets was out of whack with what was intended, and have no objection to changes being made to balance this.  Complete removal of charm from these zones however, is not an acceptable answer.
<br />

<br />
I'd just like to see some sort of aknowledgement from the devs that there is some sort of change in the works and that one of our main, class-defining (devs must hate that term by now) abilities does indeed have a future in Everquest.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
