                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Crazy idea.
<br />

<br />
Mobs "scale differently" than PCs. this is obvious.. 
<br />

<br />
charm gives you access to a differently scaled source of DPS for your group. This is broken.
<br />

<br />
Charms that break sooner is not fun. It makes it much harder to operate in a group or solo.
<br />

<br />
Here comes the crazy Idea. Charm already takes up a buff slot.. why not add some debuff components to it instead of changing the charm components? A spell one level could last for a max of 15 minutes with mild-moderate debuffs, or up to half an hour or 45 minutes with stronger debuffs. as well as have different level caps, allowing the devs to play around and try out alot of options for balance, and gives the players what they want while not breaking content.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
